result.execSummary:
The defendant Holly B Beyerl was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case. One or more other charges in this case were dismissed. The dismissed charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Holly B Beyerl is presumed innocent of the dismissed charges.

  • Holly B Beyerl was found guilty of Bail Jumping-Misdemeanor, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 946.49(1)(a).

records.addlTxt: Wis. Dept. of Corrections notice of case status change received.  Outstanding financial obligations have been satisfied.
with Elements of criminal offenses to which plea is being entered.

Defendant Holly B Beyerl in court with attorney Jorge R Fragoso.  Kevin M Osborne appeared for the State of Wisconsin.   Defendant enters a guilty plea to Count 2.  Court finds defendant guilty.  Count 1 is dismissed outright.  

Court orders the following: 
Count 2:
- 45 days straight time (1 day credit if revoked) STAYED for 1 year Probation
- Court costs of $243.00 to be paid as a condition of Probation; alternate 5 days jail
- Conditions of Probation: No alcohol/No drugs.  Submit to an AODA assessment and follow through with any treatment/counseling.  Follow thru with any treatment/counseling recommended by Agent. Be compliant with all orders of Courts with competent jurisdiction.
Jury trial - 12 person on June 10, 2014 at 08:30 am.
Jury status hearing on June 5, 2014 at 08:30 am.

Defendant Holly B Beyerl in court with attorney Jorge R. Fragoso.  Timothy A. Suha appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Atty. Fragoso requests a status/trial date. Court grants request. Defendant's matter in Washington County is still pending. Next court date in Washington County is May 19, 2014.  Court grants request for another date on this matter and will set this for status/trial.  Jury status hearing scheduled for June 5, 2014 at 08:30 am.  Jury trial - 12 person scheduled for June 10, 2014 at 08:30 am.

Defendant Holly B Beyerl in court with attorney Jorge R. Fragoso.  Debra L. Blasius appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Atty. Fragoso requests 30 days for review. Defendant has a pending case in Washington County. Court grants request.  Hearing scheduled for April 7, 2014 at 09:00 am.
Defendant is not to possess or consume any alcohol.  Defendant is not to operate a motor vehicle unless properly licensed.
Waukesha County Pretrial Screening Services Report by Wisconsin Community Services filed.

Defendant Holly B Beyerl in court, in custody, with attorney Samuel W Benedict.   Erik Krueger appeared for the State of Wisconsin.   Defendant is eligible for State Public Defender representation.  An attorney will be appointed. State to file Amended Complaint amending the Bail Jumping charge to a misdemeanor.  Court finds that this is a misdemeanor case only.  NOT GUILTY PLEA ENTERED.
